addToWhitelist(address).details: Add to the list of contracts that can get the price

initialize(address).details: This initialize replaces the constructor but it is not called automatically. It is necessary because of the upgradeability of the contracts

params._bootstrapPrice: A price to be set as a bootstraping value for this block
params._maxOraclesPerRound: The maximum count of oracles selected to participate each round
params._numIdleRounds: The number of rounds an oracle must be idle (not participating) before a removal
params._oracleManager: The contract of the oracle manager.
params._roundLockPeriodInBlocks: The minimum time span for each round before a new one can be started, in blocks.
params._tokenAddress: The address of the MOC token to use.

isSuscribed(address).details: This is designed to be called from OracleManager.

isWhitelisted(address).details: Check if an account is whitelisted

params.blockNumber: The blocknumber acting as nonce to prevent replay attacks.
params.coinpair: The coin pair to report (must match this contract)
params.sig_r: The array of R-component of Oracle signatures.
params.sig_s: The array of S-component of Oracle signatures.
params.sig_v: The array of V-component of Oracle signatures.
params.votedOracle: The address of the oracle voted as a publisher by the network.

removeFromWhitelist(address).details: Remove from the list of contracts that can get the price

setCurrentPrice(uint256).details: Sets the current price by gobernanza

suscribe(address).details: This is designed to be called from OracleManager.

params.oracleAddr: the oracle address to suscribe to this coin pair.

unsuscribe(address).details: This is designed to be called from OracleManager.

params.oracleAddr: the oracle address to suscribe to this coin pair.

devdoc.title: This contract provides an interface for feeding prices from oracles, and        get the current price. One contract must be instanced per supported coin pair,        and registered through OracleManager global contract.

canRemoveOracle(address).notice: Returns true if an oracle satisfies conditions to be removed from system.

changeIGovernor(address).notice: Change the contract's governor. Should be called through the old governance system

getCoinPair().notice: Return the coin pair for this contract

getOracleRoundInfo(address).notice: Return round information for specific oracle

getPrice().notice: Return the current price, compatible with old MOC Oracle

getWhiteListLen().notice: Returns the count of whitelisted addresses.

initialize(address).notice: Initialize the contract with the basic settings

isSuscribed(address).notice: Returns true if an oracle is suscribed to this contract' coin pair

peek().notice: Return the current price, compatible with old MOC Oracle

suscribe(address).notice: Suscribe an oracle to this coin pair , allowing it to be selected in rounds.

switchRound().notice: Switch contract context to a new round. With the objective of being a decentralized solution, this can be called by *anyone* if current round lock period is expired.

unsuscribe(address).notice: Unsuscribe an oracle from this coin pair , disallowing it to be selected in rounds.
